lasses; the 2.9.1 binary munges many internal implementation classes with leading `$` names.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Without the `--add-opens` option, basic injector construction on JDK 17+/25 can fail with `InaccessibleObjectException` from CGLIB/ReflectUtils while trying to access `ClassLoader#defineClass`.\",\n    \"The existing 2.1.7 tests are not mechanically reusable: several internal class imports no longer match the 2.9.1 artifact layout, which is the cause of the javac failure.\",\n    \"The artifact's required compile dependencies (`javax.inject:javax.inject:1` and `aopalliance:aopalliance:1.0`) are already transitive from `org.sonatype.sisu:sisu-guice:2.9.1`; optional SLF4J is not required for normal coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e1283dcfbb0b40d016a421d07f2708195a1e171bed9c70fda\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 960, "output": 681, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34409, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782717698374, "responseId": "resp_0e1283dcfbb0b40d016a421d031b5c819597c90da9b9f8bf09"}}
